sinsider.com%2Fopm-probationary-workers-fired-elon-musk-doge-trump-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOffice%20of%20Personnel%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20OPM%2C%20have%20no%20authority%20to%20fire%20low-level%20employees.%20We're%20part%20of%20a%20government%20agency%20that%20handles%20disciplinary%20actions%2C%20hiring%2C%20promotions%2C%20and%20performance%20evaluations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%20amid%20the%20layoffs%2C%20considering%20our%20workers'%20health%20problems%20is%20the%20priority%20for%20me%20as%20a%20union%20leader.%20How%20do%20you%20plan%20for%20a%20procedure%20in%20a%20month%20when%20your%20insurance%20is%20in%20question%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bfed203c-3601-4a4d-a3f2-c3eed6cef634%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20terminations%20have%20been%20of%20probationary%20employees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20employees%20who%20have%20been%20let%20go%20are%20newer%20to%20the%20National%20Park%20Service.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftook-federal-buyout-will-get-six-figure-salary-through-september-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuyout%20offer%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20still%20in%20progress.%20The%20government%20is%20proposing%20a%20RIF%2C%20or%20a%20reduction%20in%20force%2C%20which%20is%20concerning%20because%20it%20could%20affect%20everybody.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20bothers%20me%20most%20is%20that%20we%20aren't%20cogs%2C%20we're%20human%20beings.%20We%20pay%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20before%20this%2C%20and%20in%20working%20for%20the%20government%2C%20I've%20found%20the%20most%20dedicated%20workforce%20I've%20ever%20seen%2C%20filled%20with%20people%20who%20delve%20into%20their%20specialty%20with%20passion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ea2b4ee1-bf77-4d31-85e4-42906f2ba052%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20layoffs%20have%20been%20devastating%20to%20witness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20division%2C%20a%20young%20woman%20was%20doing%20a%20wonderful%20job.%20She'd%20been%20there%20eight%20or%20nine%20months%2C%20so%20she%20had%20three%20months%20left%20until%20she%20was%20no%20longer%20probationary.%20She%20received%20a%20letter%20that%20her%20work%20wasn't%20up%20to%20performance%20standards%2C%20and%20the%20next%20day%2C%20she%20arrived%20to%20pick%20up%20her%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20very%20sad%20scene.%20There%20were%20tears%2C%20and%20people%20were%20saying%20goodbye.%20She%20had%20moved%20from%20Missouri%20for%20her%20job.%20She%20had%20to%20break%20her%20lease%2C%20which%20meant%20she%20had%20to%20absorb%20a%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20week%20ago%2C%20she%20was%20reinstated%2C%20but%20she%20couldn't%20take%20her%20job%20back.%20She%20had%20already%20moved%20back%20home%2C%20and%20not%20only%20was%20it%20costly%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20emotionally%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226df8ae28-c524-4666-815e-fc73de5fb849%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20concerns%20me%20most%20is%20the%20future%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20concerned%20for%20the%20many%20young%20folks%2C%20as%20it's%20a%20young%20workforce.%20In%20the%20National%20Park%20Service%2C%20many%20employees%20have%20wanted%20to%20be%20rangers%20for%20their%20whole%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20my%20colleagues%20just%20announced%20their%20engagement.%20I'm%20so%20happy%20for%20them%2C%20but%20how%20do%20they%20plan%20for%20the%20future%20when%20they%20may%20be%20in%20a%20very%20different%20place%20next%20week%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20worried%20we%20will%20no%20longer%20attract%20the%20best%20and%20the%20brightest.%20It's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20who%20would%20advise%20their%20children%20to%20get%20a%20job%20in%20the%20federal%20government%20and%20be%20treated%20like%20this.%20I%20think%20the%20people%20in%20charge%20don't%20understand%20the%20ramifications%20of%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%20or%20they%20don't%20care.%20The%20American%20people%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%